New elected president of NS CIOFF of Montenegro and executive board is Nedzad Lekic. Dusan Banjevic decided not to candidate again after 16 years of being president of NS CIOFF of Montenegro. As a vice president Danijela Bokan was elected. As an assembly president Emin Haxhi has been elected, and for the executive board members, next to the president, there are six members elected:
-Boban Banjevic (Folk ensemble "Aluminium");
-Marko Djokic (Folk ensemble "Zahumlje");
-Danijela Bokan (Folk ensemble "Njegos");
-Predrag Susic (Folk ensemble "Nikola Djurkovic");
-Nemanja Pudar (Folk ensemble "Sloga");
-Jovica Kaludjerovic (Folk ensemble "Crna Gora");

Secretary will be decided in the future period.
